    Who was George W Bush up against?
    Bush, a Republican from Texas and the eldest son of George H. W. Bush, took office following a narrow victory over Democratic incumbent vice president Al Gore in the 2000 presidential election. Four years later, in the 2004 presidential election, he defeated Democrat nominee John Kerry to win re-election.

    Was George W Bush popular?
    Bush began his presidency with approval ratings near 50%. Following the September 11 attacks, Bush held approval ratings of greater than 85%, among the highest for any President.

    When was George Bush head of the CIA?
    After a pledge by Bush not to run for either president or vice president in 1976, opposition to his nomination died down. Bush served as the DCI for 355 days, from January 30, 1976, to January 20, 1977.

    About
    georgewbush.com

    Description

    George Walker Bush is an American politician who served as the 43rd president of the United States from 2001 to 2009. A member of the Republican Party, he previously served as the 46th governor of Texas from 1995 to 2000. Wikipedia
    Born: 6 July 1946 (age 77 years), New Haven, Connecticut, United States
    Presidential term: 20 January 2001 20 January 2009
    Party: Republican Party
    Vice president: Dick Cheney (20012009)
    Spouse: Laura Bush (m. 1977)
    Children: Jenna Bush Hager, Barbara Bush
    Siblings: Jeb Bush, Pauline Robinson Bush, Dorothy Bush Koch, Marvin Bush, Neil Bush
